Phase 1: Preparation (Gathering Your Tools)
Before touching any code, you need to set up the accounts and services that will power the bot.

Activate the VPN (Crucial):

Turn on your VPN (e.g., NordVPN or Proton) on your PC and connect to a server in Switzerland or the Netherlands.

Verification Check: Go to ipinfo.io in your browser to confirm your IP address reflects the chosen country.

Prepare the Wallet:

Ensure you have the MetaMask extension installed in your browser.

Make sure you have your 100 USDC and a couple of MATIC/POL (to pay for network micro-fees) on the Polygon Mainnet.

Export your Private Key from MetaMask. (Never share this with anyone or upload it online).

Generate Polymarket APIs:

With the VPN active, log into Polymarket.com.

Go to Settings -> API Keys.

Create a new key and securely save the API Key, the Secret, and the Passphrase. They will only be shown to you once!

Get the "Brains" (Alchemy & Groq):

Go to Alchemy.com, create a free account, set up a new App (choose Polygon Mainnet as the network), and copy the RPC URL (the link starting with https://).

Go to console.groq.com, log in, navigate to "API Keys," and generate a new key to access Llama 3 for free.

Phase 2: Building the Base (The Files)
Now let's create the bot's home on your computer.

Create a new folder on your Desktop (e.g., name it PolyBot).

Inside this folder, create these 3 empty text files (ensure they don't have hidden extensions like .txt.py):

main.py

requirements.txt

.env

Paste the code:

Open main.py with Notepad (or better, a real code editor like VS Code) and paste the complete Python code I generated for you earlier.

Open requirements.txt and paste the list of the 5 required libraries.

Phase 3: The Secret Core (The .env file)
This is the most delicate step. If there is a typo here, the bot won't connect.

Open the .env file and fill in each field exactly as shown, without any weird spacing or quotation marks. It should look like this:

Snippet di codice
PK=paste_your_long_metamask_private_key_here
POLY_ADDRESS=0xYourPublicMetamaskAddressHere
CLOB_API_KEY=your_polymarket_api_key_here
CLOB_SECRET=your_polymarket_secret_here
CLOB_PASSPHRASE=your_polymarket_passphrase_here

ALCHEMY_RPC_URL=https://polygon-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/your_alchemy_key_here
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_groq_key_here

STARTING_CAPITAL=100.0
Phase 4: The Launch (Ignition)
We are ready. It's time to run everything.

Open your Terminal (or Command Prompt):

On Windows: Search for cmd in the Start menu.

On Mac: Search for Terminal using Spotlight.

Navigate to the bot's folder:
Type cd followed by the path to your folder (e.g., cd Desktop/PolyBot) and press Enter.

Install the "Fuel" (The Dependencies):
In the terminal, type this command and press Enter:

Bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Wait for it to download and install everything. It should take about a minute.

Start the Bot:
(Final check: Is the VPN on and set to Switzerland? Good.)
Type this command and press Enter:

Bash
python main.py
What happens next?
If you did everything correctly, your terminal will come to life and you will start seeing:

🚀 Inizializzazione Polymarket Sniper Bot... (Or the English equivalent if you translated the print statements).

✅ Connesso a Polygon...

The bot will then enter a silent standby mode, scanning blocks until it spots a transaction from one of the Whale addresses you put in the code.
